This paper is about a neural machine translation method, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method also involves optimization using an algorithm called Connectionist Temporal Classification (CTC), which is commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The paper also introduces an objective function and uses neural networks, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to simultaneous translation, which involves processing and analyzing visual data (cs.CV).
